                                            <content type="html">
                            &lt;p&gt;Both your comments definitely strikes home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since it was during work-hours, I feel some of the participants - from whom those complaints came from - were not completely freely joining the party ; that could be part of the explanation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3 sessions sure isn&#039;t enough, but most of the participants already picked up the ball after the first round. They got the idea and played along really well. I might have had a large numbers of &quot;early adopters&quot; in the group which led me into thinking it was understood by all.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For the constraints part, we mostly focused on getting everybody onboard with TDD and then on expressing intent. I guess I was not poking around hard enough so that their focus would shift from the problem to the constraints.&lt;/p&gt;
