                    <title>I&#039;ve run into this as well. T…</title>
                    <link rel="alternate" href="http://coderetreat.org/xn/detail/6456126:Comment:10439"/>
                                        <id>tag:coderetreat.org,2012-06-25:6456126:Comment:10439</id>
                                        <updated>2012-06-25T14:59:45.956Z</updated>
                    
                                            <author>
                            <name>Matt Steele</name>
                            <uri>http://coderetreat.org/profile/MattSteele</uri>
                        </author>
                    
                    <summary type="html">
                        &lt;p&gt;I&#039;ve run into this as well. This seemed to happen less when the group was self-selected (i.e. we did it over a weekend) than when we tried with a bigger group during a workday. Not sure why this was. Maybe the fact that you weren&#039;t eating into work time made people relax a bit more?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I don&#039;t have a great solution, though I think framing the day way can help. The &lt;a href=&quot;http://coderetreat-omaha.heroku.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;slide deck&lt;/a&gt; I used at the start of my last Code Retreat…&lt;/p&gt;                    </summary>

                                            <content type="html">
                            &lt;p&gt;I&#039;ve run into this as well. This seemed to happen less when the group was self-selected (i.e. we did it over a weekend) than when we tried with a bigger group during a workday. Not sure why this was. Maybe the fact that you weren&#039;t eating into work time made people relax a bit more?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I don&#039;t have a great solution, though I think framing the day way can help. The &lt;a href=&quot;http://coderetreat-omaha.heroku.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;slide deck&lt;/a&gt; I used at the start of my last Code Retreat spent a fair amount of time explaining that you *will* delete your code, and the session is *designed* to keep you from finishing. This helped some people get into the right mindset.&lt;/p&gt;                        </content>
                    
